parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and environmental damage. It can also lead to property damage, personal injury, and embarrassment.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the filler neck when the tank is full
fuel overflows onto the vehicle's exterior and ground
fuel pump nozzle clicks off but fuel continues to flow
fuel spills onto the owner's clothes and shoes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Inlet Check Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank inlet check valve can cause gasoline to splash back out of the fuel filler neck, creating a hazardous situation for the person filling the vehicle and others nearby. This can lead to accidents, injuries, and environmental damage.
symptoms: Gasoline splashes back out of the fuel filler neck when the gas pump automatically shuts off
causing a puddle of gasoline on the ground
and potentially splashing the person filling the vehicle. The fuel tank overflows

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent shaking of the steering wheel, also known as the "Death Wobble," can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: the front end of the vehicle wobbles
and the vehicle may become difficult to control

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Rust and Steering Gearbox Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering gearbox due to frame rust can cause loss of steering control, accidents, and potentially lead to fatalities.
symptoms: steering gearbox separation from the frame
